title: Appointment text is missing in invitation mails
content:
Hello all,

in invitations the appointment text is missing if I send the invitation with Thunderbird. If I send it with Outlook, the text is visible at the receiver side.

Unfortunately, this bug keeps me from using Thunderbird. How am I supposed to send invitations if the recipient can't see the content?

Greetings

title: Indexation of emails
content:
Hi, since a few weeks ago, Thunderbird started to index emails. Addiotionally, the indexation is not being done correctly since some responses to a given email appear indexed to another different initial email. I already removed the selection of indexation option in settings, general but the problem remains.

The program has always worked fine without this option being activated and I want to keep in that way. Therefore, I request help to: i) remove indexation in future emails; ii) remove the already existing indexation.

My version is 102.8.0 (32-bit).

Thanks for developing the program and helping with this problem, Joaquim
creator: pratas.leitao

title: How to select S/MIME as default for new messages
content:
Hello,

I have been experimenting with OpenPGP and S/MIME to see what fits best for my use case and decided to go with my S/MIME certificate. It works fine, I de-selected the PGP settings and removed the key, but for new emails, it still defaults to selecting PGP for digital signing, etc. Because no key is present it just does nothing. I need to manually click that button and choose S/MIME every time. `

Is there no way to have S/MIME as the default for new messages?

I have attached how the new email window looks by default and my end-to-end encryption settings. I would greatly appreciate any helpful directions on where to change the default. I searched through settings and online but found nothing about this.

Thanks! Paul
creator: arkensor

title: Come revocare l'autorizzazione ai contenuti remoti di un messaggio che siano stati autorizzati per errore?
content:
Salve, come da oggetto, recentemente, causa distrazione, mi è capitato di aver autorizzato per errore i contenuti remoti dalle sorgenti di un messaggio indesiderato, e nonostante abbia tentato in tutti i modi di tornare indietro sui miei passi (almeno per gli eventuali sucessivi messaggi indesiderati aventi contenuti remoti provenienti dalle medesime fonti), non ci sono riuscito, e non so neppure se aver successivamente flaggato quello specifico messaggio come indesiderato, possa aver automaticamente annullato l'erronea operazione precedente. Pertanto le mie domande sono le seguenti:

- Come si può revocare l'autorizzazione precedentemente concessa ai contenuti remoti di un messaggio che siano stati autorizzati per errore o per ripensamento?

- Non sarebbe possibile fare in modo che la barra delle notifiche che contiene il pulsante "Opzioni", ospitante le impostazioni relative ai contenuti remoti di ogni massaggio, rimanga visibile anche dopo aver eventualmente optato per una delle possibili autorizzazioni, in modo da poter tornare velocemente sui propri passi, o poter scegliere una diversa opzione, cambiando eventualmente solo l'aspetto della medesima una volta che si è flaggata una delle opzioni disponibili (anziché farla sparire)?

Grazie mille per qualsiasi supporto. Cordiali saluti
creator: robikerki

title: Gmail folders appearing under non-Gmail accounts
content:
I have several email addresses that are not Gmail. Under each email account in Thunderbird, the usual folders appear - Inbox, Drafts, Sent, Spam and Deleted. But then there is a folder labelled [Gmail], in italics, which when opened shows a string of other folders. Thunderbird set up each account automatically; I did not touch the settings. Could someone please explain why those Gmail folders are appearing, what is their purpose and can I safely delete them?

Also - I have one Gmail account that I now wish to add to Thunderbird. Will that affect the Gmail folders under the non-Gmail accounts?

My Thunderbird version is 102.8.0

Many thanks for the help.

title: Thunderbird 111.0b2 css file location
content:
I'm not digging the new look and the extra animations are annoying to say the least. Not looking to be entertained just read and respond to emails. They increased the white space in the folder view which is annoying and unnecessary but the messages view is a bible style single spaced that is almost unreadable. I found the CSS properties needed to make things readable again; however, can't find the location of the CSS files. I do have the legacy stylesheet option on and have the userChrome.css file (both in a chrome folder and hanging lose in the profile folder) but it's not working. Also tried changing the settings for fonts but this changes everything so increasing to make the messages view readable makes the folder view scream at you

it's telling me the properties are in two files; chrome://messenger/skin/shared/threadPane.css and chrome://messenger/skin/about3Pane.css, but can't find these anywhere on my system. Does anyone know where the actual path to these files are? Or does anyone have an idea why the userChrome.css file isn't working? On Windows 10 22H2 for reference

title: Message filters automatically deleted
content: I buily a month's worth of message filters. Despite doing everything I could to enter the data correctly, several problems keep happening. 1. I enter the data into the filter spot, I press the Enter key instead of closing the message filter entry window because just closing the window does NOT sabve anything. I select "Run Now" and nothing happens becauze the data is not saved. If I do an edit, the data I just entered is not there. 2. I open Message Filters to add in data. Inside Message Filters, there are one to several empty message filter lines. I cannot tell if there was data in the line that was not saved of if simply opening the Message Filters made an arbitrary new, empty entry somewhere. 3. I apparently stupidly tried to see if trouble shooting Message Filters would help. I clicked on Troubleshoot and see that Message Filters might be disabled. I thought I got outr of troubleshooting. When I did, a month's worth of Message Filters were erased. All I have now is "Mark e-mails from Cardbook", the useless because there are no data fields populated "mozilla temporary", and "SpamAssassinYes"/ Hundreds of entries wiped out. How to I stop from losing this material in the future, and, better yet, why can this happen. Why would you erase everything without even a warning?
creator: ADougRay1

title: New CardDAV address book to sync Google contacts - "Failed to connect" error message
content:
I have followed this tutorial in order to have my Google contacts sync with Thunderbird with a CardDAV address book: [https://ekiwi-blog.de/en/25881/synchr.../synchronize-google-calendar-and-contacts-with-thunderbird-without-addons/]

On one of my computers this works brilliantly. On the other, after allowing Thunderbird access to my Google account I repeatedly get the error message “Failed to connect”. Please see attached screenshots.

I am connected to the Internet. I am 100% sure of my password and that it has been entered correctly. My Thunderbird is the latest version for my system (version 102.7.1). What could be the problem?

Many thanks.

(P.S. I have successfully Synced my Google Calendar with Thunderbird using iCal and CalDav so there should be no connection issue.)

title: Missing folders
content:
I'm running Thunderbird 102.8.0 (64-bit) on MacOS 13.2.1 Ventura. I just migrated from Google to Apple by dragging and dropping folders using Thunderbird yet somehow when I run TB now, only 11 of roughly 75 folders are visible. I've removed and re-added the Apple email and it's made no difference.

I've removed the Apple email, closed TB, deleted session.json and foldertree.json files, started TB, re-added the Apple email account, and I STILL only see the same folders.

Please help. I really don't want to have to move to Outlook.

Ken
creator: Ken.Hemmerling

title: Needing Help With Thunderbird Error Message
content: Lately, whenever I click "SEND" to in T-Bird, I am getting an error message that I've never seen before. This has never happened till recently and I don't know what to do to resolve it. All help will be appreciated.

title: Problems with T-Bird Client
content:
When I open T-Bird on one of my laptops, it will not download any emails, and the icon left of "inbox" just keeps endlessly swimming back & forth horizontally.

Additionally, whenever I click "SEND" on an email message, I get the error message below in the screenshot. How can I resolve this issue? Any & all help appreciated.
creator: jayp1966

title: ?  Enter your password for [email]@bigpond.com on imap.telstra.com
content:
Enter your password for [email]@bigpond.com on imap.telstra.com

After entering my password Thunderbird continues to ask this question and so of course will not let me in on my laptop or my mobile. I have checked absolutely everything I can think of in my limited understanding, including account settings which tells me my password is the correct one to use. I can get into my emails for [email]@bigpond.com through the Telstra webmail which is not very convenient and doesn't seem to allow me to to see all the files I have on the Thunderbird app.

The main email address I use is the one above not the one I have logged in to send this message. I seem to be able to receive emails on [email]@gmail.com but I use the Microsoft app to receive them. It also is regularly saying that I need to update my gmail account and even when I do that it still keeps giving me a msg to say the same thing.

I am at a loss as to know what to do without deleting the Thunderbird app which means I will lose everything I have there.

Do hope you are able to help. And I thank you for your time. Regards Gillian Dickinson
creator: fangd1966

title: Firefox enrollment
content: Hi. I followed directions to open a Thunderbird account, [edited] @fencemail.com. As required, I paid for a Domain Name: [edited] @micalone.org, from Ghandi, including a VAT Tax. I got an intercept, that a problematical HTML(?) was missing, whatever it is, with nary a hint nor link to fix the problem. Horrors! Unfortunately, I am not a computer whiz, and most computer technical verbiage is like hieroglyphics to me. I am in a dilemma in that I do not have the proffered Internet address. Do to a nasty virus, I no longer have access to my old ISP address, [edited] @juno.com, hence the need to open the highly recommended Thunderbird account. So, I can not send or receive email to resolve this HTML problem. Is the U.S. Postal Service a viable option? If so. my postal address is: Nick Micalone, [removed address information from public]. If someone is intimately familiar with the Thunderbird enrolling process, I will gladly pre-pay for the postage and associated costs for a fix by simple instructions. If this helps, I do have the Thunderbird logo on my desktop. Hopefully, the Thunderbird wizards can fix this remotely, at their end. Best regards, Nick M.
creator: njnicholas.micalone
